 to specific enemy types<br/>-the game crashed after I beat the final boss, and since it\'s a roguelike it treats that as a quit so all my items are gone and I don\'t have the patience to try again to a possible identity result<br/><br/>For an ecchi game I\'d give it a 7/10, for a game-game I\'d give it about a 4/10. I wonder how the Z game will be.','I just finished playing Omega Labyrinth on vita (note that it\'s the first one, not the Z game that was supposed to be released in the West a couple months ago but wasn\'t due to all that controversy)\r\nIt was never localized, but there\'s a fan translation which you\'ll need some patching software to use. \r\n\r\nPros:\r\n-good art, voices\r\n-I really like some of the characters like Marika\r\n-the breast size tying into character strength is nice\r\n-I really like being able to touch and jiggle their breasts even when the characters are in the middle of conversation\r\n-there\'s a breast-massaging minigame to identify items that\'s really arousing\r\n-for a roguelike it\'s really forgiving, although this might be a con if you like the hardcore stuff. getting the \'return to base with all stuff\' item is really easy and there\'s also a \'return to base on death when held\' item\r\n-pretty good pacing\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n-poor enemy variety\r\n-equipment is really simplified, the main damage traits are just bonus damage to specific enemy types\r\n-the game crashed after I beat the final boss, and since it\'s a roguelike it treats that as a quit so all my items are gone and I don\'t have the patience to try again to a possible identity result\r\n\r\nFor an ecchi game I\'d give it a 7/10, for a game-game I\'d give it about a 4/10. I wonder how the Z game will be.',1544245076,1544608965,'[{\"name\":\"8132E1p3wnL._SX342_.jpg\",\"type\":\"image\\/jpeg\",\"tmp_name\":\"\\/tmp\\/phpncbixH\",\"error\":0,\"size\":51058,\"filename\":\"8132E1p3wnL._SX342_.jpg\",\"extension\":\"jpg\",\"file_id\":\"1544245076904\",\"file\":\"15442450